# UI Components

**ABSOLUTE RULE: shadcn/ui is the ONLY permitted UI component library in this project. No custom UI components, no plain HTML elements, no other component libraries — ever.**

This means:
- Never write custom button, input, card, dialog, badge, or any other UI component from scratch
- Never use raw HTML elements like `<button>`, `<input>`, `<select>`, `<textarea>`, `<a>` (styled or unstyled) for UI
- Never reach for another library (Radix directly, Headless UI, MUI, Chakra, etc.)
- If shadcn/ui doesn't have what you need, find the closest shadcn/ui primitive and extend it

## Setup

If shadcn/ui is not initialized in the project:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding Components

If a specific component hasn't been added yet, install it before using it:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

Examples:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
npx shadcn@latest add card
npx shadcn@latest add input
npx shadcn@latest add dialog
```

Components are installed to `src/components/ui/` and can be imported from there:

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card";

// ❌ BAD — raw HTML, never do this
<button className="...">Click me</button>

// ❌ BAD — custom component built from scratch, never do this
function MyButton({ children }) {
  return <div className="cursor-pointer rounded bg-blue-500 px-4 py-2">{children}</div>;
}
```

## Clerk Auth — Buttons & Modals

Clerk sign-in and sign-up UI **must** follow these rules:

1. **Always use shadcn `<Button>` for sign-in/sign-up triggers** — never Clerk's default `<SignInButton>` or `<SignUpButton>` rendered as-is without wrapping in a shadcn `Button`.
2. **Always open Clerk auth in a modal** — set `mode="modal"` on `<SignInButton>` and `<SignUpButton>`.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — shadcn Button triggers Clerk modal
import { SignInButton, SignUpButton } from "@clerk/nextjs";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>

<SignUpButton mode="modal">
  <Button variant="outline">Sign Up</Button>
</SignUpButton>

// ❌ BAD — Clerk default button without shadcn wrapper
<SignInButton />

// ❌ BAD — redirect-based flow instead of modal
<SignInButton mode="redirect">
  <Button>Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>
```
